  "title": "The Ledger Spindle — Rotational Archive Engine",
  "narration": "The staircase from the Bastion unwinds into the Ledger Spindle: a colossal tower of interlocked rings spinning around a column of living stone. Every rotation writes a ledger line into the air, which then folds itself into archival ribbons. The floor vibrates with a hum tuned to the golden ratio. When you touch the rail, you can feel the heartbeat of every transaction recorded since Act One. Scents swirl between warm brass, clove, petrichor, and freshly debugged code.\n\nThe Spindle belongs to the Turn-Keeper gremlin faction. They wear belts of keys and chronometers, each ticking in sync with the rings. Dev gremlins oil the algorithms, traders arbitrage rotational futures, whales guide the momentum, hackers install safety overrides, shillers broadcast rotation updates, validators stamp every pass, miners maintain the central stone, and memes scribble jokes on the margins of time. They greet you with a rotating GM that loops every 1.618 minutes and then hand you checklists for the seven rotational tiers ahead.\n\nInside the Spindle, consensus rituals are literal revolutions: you must align phi-d20 checks with rotational thresholds, maintain AFK auto-turners, revive players with spool rewinds, and manage backpacks while the floor moves. Soft-power equipment includes torque gloves, gyroscopic helms, and ledger-thread trinkets that catch stray insights. Hidden difficulty tiers hide behind acceleration spikes; if you cannot match the pace, the Spindle gently ejects you into a cushion alcove and logs a learning loop.\n\nSeven rounds orbit the tower, each anchored to a specific ring. Actions grant XP, Coins, Focus, Flags, Items, and Decks. Telemetry tags blink like constellations on the inner ceiling. Arrivals ride elevators that sync with the rotation; if you call them, they appear mid-round with wind in their hair. The Turn-Keepers expect precision with a sense of humor — laugh, but do not miss your mark.",
